    <h3 id="academic">Academic</h3>

    <p>If you are somewhat familiar with Jekyll already, you may want to jumping right in with Academic Pages. It’s not exactly simple, but its versatile.</p>

    <p><img src="https://imgur.com/JpASy3c.png" alt="" /></p>

    <p>I tried <a href="https://github.com/search?q=hugo+theme">github.com/search?q=hugo+theme</a>, and found that Academic has a toooon of stars. More even than the repository for all of hugos themes in one place !!!</p>

    <p><img src="https://imgur.com/25btYyt.png" alt="" /></p>

    <p>There is a one click fork\deploy with GitHub\GitLab Pages and Netlify.</p>

    <p>Seriously just click a button, it creates the repo and publishes it for you.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/install/">Academic Install</a>
        <blockquote>
          <p>You can choose from one of the following four methods to install:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>one-click install using your web browser (recommended)</li>
            <li>install on your computer using Git with the Command Prompt/Terminal app</li>
            <li>install on your computer by downloading the ZIP files</li>
            <li>install on your computer with RStudio</li>
          </ul>
        </blockquote>
      </li>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/writing-markdown-latex/">Writing content with Markdown, LaTeX, and Shortcodes</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/page-builder/">Getting Started With the Page Builder</a> - Learn Academic’s widget system.</li>
      <li><a href="https://lmyint.github.io/post/hugo-academic-tips/">Academic Tips</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/jupyter/">Display Jupyter Notebooks with Academic</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/managing-content/#create-a-course-or-documentation">Creating a Course or Documentation</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://sourcethemes.com/academic/docs/migrate-from-jekyll/">Academic - Migrate From Jekyll</a></li>
    </ul>

